Newcastle United target Diego Carlos has handed in an official transfer request at Sevilla, according to reports. Newcastle want to sign at least one central defender before the end of the January transfer window. And Carlos is at the top of their wishlist. Lille star Sven Botman was wanted by Newcastle earlier this month. But the Ligue 1 side refused to do business over the Dutchman in this window. Newcastle ‘Lodge £25m Bid’ For Duvan Zapata Liverpool Set Origi Price As Newcastle Make Approach Carlos has been key at the back for Sevilla in a side that currently sit second in La Liga. But it appears the lure of playing in the Premier League as well as a huge pay rise is enough for the Brazilian to want to move to St James’ Park. Sky Sports News reporter Kaveh Solhekol says Carlos has made it clear he wants to join Newcastle. And now the 28-year-old has made an official request to Sevilla to leave this month. Sky Sports News reporter Kaveh Solhekol said: “We were just talking about Diego Carlos, I just told you that the player wants to move to Newcastle. POLL “And just now I’ve been told that the player has officially asked to leave Sevilla. “Diego Carlos has asked to leave Sevilla, he wants to move to Newcastle. “I told you the player wants to come, Sevilla willing to do business, but the price must be right for them.” Solhekol then received further information that Carlos will write an email to the Sevilla president and manager requesting his exit be facilitated.